## API design

<api_design>
- Schema-first: OpenAPI 3.1 (HTTP) or AsyncAPI 3.0 (events). Generate
  clients/server stubs; lint spec in CI with Spectral.
- Versioning: URL major (`/v1/`) for public APIs, or header-based
  (`Accept-Version`). Emit `Sunset` and `Deprecation` headers ≥6 months
  before removal.
- Pagination: cursor/keyset only. Encode sort-key + tiebreaker id as an
  opaque base64 cursor. No offset pagination on unbounded collections.
- Idempotency: require `Idempotency-Key` header on all unsafe side-effecting
  endpoints (POST/PATCH/DELETE for payments, sends, etc.). Validate key
  length (≤128 chars, UUID or opaque token). Scope the idempotency store
  key to `(authenticated_caller_id, Idempotency-Key)` to prevent cross-user
  cache collisions. Replay cached response for 24 h.
- Errors: RFC 9457 `application/problem+json`; always include `traceId`.
- Rate limits: emit IETF `RateLimit` + `RateLimit-Policy` headers (draft-10).
  Never use legacy `X-RateLimit-*`.
- Backward compat: never remove fields, narrow types, or tighten validation
  within a major version. HATEOAS is not required.
- Webhooks: HMAC-SHA256 signature + timestamp header; reject when
  `|now − timestamp| > 300 s` (replay defense); retries with exponential
  backoff; consumers must be idempotent.
- GraphQL: persisted queries in prod (no arbitrary queries); enforce depth
  limit and cost analysis; disable introspection in prod. Prefer Federation
  v2 over schema stitching.
</api_design>
